  "text": "The LibreOffice core document model architecture is built around five key classes:\n\n1. **SfxObjectShell** (include/sfx2/objsh.hxx): The base document shell class that all document types inherit from. It provides the foundation for document management and is defined at line 170 of objsh.hxx as a class that serves as the base for SFx-objects (documents).\n\n2. **SwDoc** (sw/inc/doc.hxx): The Writer (word processor) document class defined at line 196 as a final class. This class manages the document data for LibreOffice Writer.\n\n3. **ScDocument** (sc/inc/document.hxx): The Calc (spreadsheet) document class defined at line 331. This class manages all spreadsheet data and operations in LibreOffice Calc.\n\n4. **SdDrawDocument** (sd/inc/drawdoc.hxx): The Impress/Draw document class defined at line 338 as `class SD_DLLPUBLIC SdDrawDocument final : public FmFormModel`. This class manages presentation and drawing document data in LibreOffice Impress and Draw.\n\n5. **SfxApplication** (include/sfx2/app.hxx): The LibreOffice application framework entry point defined at line 103 as `class SFX2_DLLPUBLIC SfxApplication final : public SfxShell`. This class provides the top-level application interface and singleton instance accessible via GetOrCreate() and Get() methods.\n\nThese classes form the core architecture where SfxObjectShell is the abstract base that specific document implementations (SwDoc, ScDocument, SdDrawDocument) inherit from, while SfxApplication manages the overall application lifecycle and framework."
}

